BERLIN (AP) — Four men, some of them suspected right-wing extremists, were arrested Thursday as German investigators raided their homes in a probe of suspicions that they acquired substances to build an explosive device, police said.Investigators seized raw material for explosives, firecrackers, cellphones and a substantial quantity of narcotics in the raids on the four apartments in Cologne, according to a police statement. The men were to be brought before a judge for a decision on whether they can be kept in custody over the drug find.Police didn’t give further details beyond saying that the men were between the ages of 36 and 53.